review_blob: Bottle. Hazy amber colour, head is moderate. Aroma is a wee bit pungent with citrus on the side. A fair amount of sweetness in the taste not as hoppy as I would like.

Bottle. Nice orange colour with medium head. Aroma is grass, pine and hops.
Bitter taste with a hint of malts. I was expecting more out of this one to be honest.

Bottle. Medium head, nice amber colour. Aroma is great, citrus and caramel. Taste is no way near the aroma, its a deceiving brew. Carbonation is overpowering, like Pop Rocks in your mouth and the bitterness doesnt come thru.

Bottle from Systembolaget, bought March 2012. Had one then and one now, very similar although its been sitting in the basement for a year. Pours dark brown/black, head is pale. The aroma is abundant with coffe and a touch of vanilla, hard roasted like. The mouthfeel is dissapointing, very thin, annoyingly intesive carbonation. Cold coffe comes to mind.

Bottle at OT, Stockholm. Amber colour with a white head. Citrus nose lot of hops. Taste is fresh and rich.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
